- cocos2d-x version: 3.14.1

Hello.
I'm trying to reduce the number of draw calls in my UI, and add all bitmap fonts with sprites in one UI atlas. When you initialize the font with constructor and don't change font size it works fine, but when you change font size, his texture coordinates back to the zero position. After hour analysis of engine code I found the problem. If you change the font size of the texture coordinates will melt Vec2 :: ZERO.

```
void Label::setBMFontSizeInternal(float fontSize)
{
    if(_currentLabelType == LabelType::BMFONT){
        this->setBMFontFilePath(_bmFontPath, Vec2::ZERO, fontSize);
        _contentDirty = true;
    }
}
```
In my case the solution was to change the function that creates the Label.
Your function:
```
Label* Label::createWithBMFont(const std::string& bmfontFilePath, const std::string& text,const TextHAlignment& hAlignment /* = TextHAlignment::LEFT */, int maxLineWidth /* = 0 */, const Vec2& imageOffset /* = Vec2::ZERO */)
{
    auto ret = new (std::nothrow) Label(hAlignment);
    if (ret && ret->setBMFontFilePath(bmfontFilePath,imageOffset))
    ...
```
to:
```
Label* Label::createWithBMFont(const std::string& bmfontFilePath, const std::string& text,const TextHAlignment& hAlignment /* = TextHAlignment::LEFT */, int maxLineWidth /* = 0 */, const Vec2& imageOffset /* = Vec2::ZERO */, float fontSize)
{
    auto ret = new (std::nothrow) Label(hAlignment);
   if (ret && ret->setBMFontFilePath(bmfontFilePath,imageOffset, fontSize))
   ...
```
Can you solve this problem. My function only fix font size on initialization, but when you change it on runtime it work wrong.

- cocos2d-x version: 3.13.1
- devices test on: Lenovo TAB S8-50F
- developing environments
   - NDK version: 11c

Steps to Reproduce:


The problem occurs only when the App is stopped (onStop), killed and than created (onCreate) again.
The left side on the [Android Lifecyle](http://www.javatpoint.com/images/androidimages/Android-Activity-Lifecycle.png). 

If these steps are executed depends on the system and the currently available resources. 

This is the message from the logs:
`01-18 13:32:04.733 29461-29640/de.truncad.trunapp A/libc: Fatal signal 11 (SIGSEGV), code 1, fault addr 0x24 in tid 29640 (GLThread 1112)`

Cause: 
The problem is caused by Label::setTTFConfig. I added the following code to the HelloWorld Demo and had the same problems: 
```
    std::string label2Font = "fonts/Marker Felt.ttf";
    TTFConfig label_config;
    label_config.distanceFieldEnabled = false;
    label_config.fontSize = 1; 
    label_config.fontFilePath = label2Font;
    label_config.outlineSize = 0;
    
    auto label2 = Label::createWithTTF("asdf", label2Font, 1, Size(10,10));

    label2->setTTFConfig(label_config);
    this->addChild(label2);
```
If  `label2->setTTFConfig(label_config);` is removed it works.
